<item>
            <title>[HBASE-273] Provide capability for client specified time stamps in HBase</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-273</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently all records stored in HBase are given a time stamp derived from the current time. It should be possible for the client to specify the time stamp.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, if a web crawler is storing page contents in HBase, it should be able to set the time stamp to the crawl time which is not necessarily &apos;now&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12372526">HBASE-273</key>
            <summary>Provide capability for client specified time stamps in HBase</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png">Bug</type>
